Diagnosis of abdominal malignancy by radiologic fine-needle aspiration biopsy. Fine needle aspiration biopsy in 100 consecutive patients with suspected abdominal malignancy yielded a positive diagnosis in 69 (82%) of 84 patients in cases ultimately proven to have cancer in the area sampled. Of 21 pancreatic cancers, 18 (86%) were detected 24 (83%) of 29 liver lesions, usually metastases, were identifed